Today's Diplomatic News Highlights 
Following are today's diplomatic news highlights:
Chinese Premier Meets Bulgarian FM
Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji, in a meeting with Bulgarian Foreign
Minister Nadezhda Mikhailova here today, said that relations between
China and Bulgaria have enjoyed a steady growthin the past five decades
since the two countries established diplomatic ties.
Zhu said that China appreciates Bulgaria's adherence to the " one
China" policy and that the two countries have broad prospects for their
cooperation in the economic and trade fields.
Chinese Senior Military Officers Meet Mongolian Guests
Chinese Defense Minister Chi Haotian, in a meeting with visiting
Dashzebeg, Chief of General Staff of the Mongolian Armed Forces, said
that China will work together with Mongolia to transform their over
4,000 kilometer long border into one featuring prosperity, harmony and
friendship.
Fu Quanyou, chief of General Staff of the Chinese People's Liberation
Army, also held talks here today with Dashzebeg and emphasized that the
developing relationship between China and Mongolia tallies with the
fundamental interest of both peoples, and helps promote peace and
stability in the region and the world at large.
Friendly Exchanges
Xiao Yang, president of the Supreme People's Court, met today with a
delegation of the Supreme Constitutional Court of Egypt led by justice
Wahid Mahmoud Ibrahim.
He Luli, vice chairperson of the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress and president of the Chinese People's Association for
Peace and Disarmament, met here today with a delegation headed by
N.A.Razzak Hussain, secretary-general of the Afro-Asian People's
Solidarity Organization.
